<script data-th="server" id="thd-helmet__script--productStructureData" type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org/","@type":"Product","name":"Samsung 24 in. 4.0 cu. ft. Vented Smart Dial Electric Dryer in White with Sensor Dry DV25B6900EW","image":["https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/ff95a9e0-e61b-4144-97ff-1c9e9fa8300a/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-64_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/ded83cfd-e86b-42ba-8ad4-fd74da0bd9f9/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-e1_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/a1db4951-c896-4669-9caa-ba3d6cbdf1cf/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-a0_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/82efb9df-35a6-4fd7-afc3-614aaa0106e8/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-1d_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/4fdd1fa6-fbff-45a4-873c-5d60f5c5f4dc/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-66_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/989ec93a-08f7-41cc-9f21-207635ec1f55/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-77_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/c99f7ad3-b4c9-43e0-b4dc-487ede1f2006/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-c3_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/f23cac31-4720-4364-9195-e70260f36e78/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-4f_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/fb95c7d2-6ffa-47dc-ac81-4a24f06c789c/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-1f_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/2a62858d-ee8b-441b-bc94-ce9143a36178/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-44_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/2c935220-8c15-4a4f-b53b-b92557420f60/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-fa_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/48cfbd6c-dc17-49d4-a61d-0899c98276b9/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-d4_100.jpg","https://images.thdstatic.com/productImages/776f84af-f1df-49e9-bfd3-562b86797c75/svn/white-samsung-electric-dryers-dv25b6900ew-31_100.jpg"],"description":"Samsung's 4.0 cu. ft. Large Capacity Electric Dryer is equipped with our AI Smart Dial, which learns and recommends your favorite cycles and simplifies the control panel to make controlling your dryer a breeze. It is also Wi-Fi Connected, so you can get end of cycle alerts, remotely start, schedule and more from your smartphone with the SmartThings App.","productID":"323095575","sku":"1009225402","gtin13":"0887276665184","model":"DV25B6900EW","depth":"43.3 in","height":"33.5 in","width":"23.62 in","color":"White","weight":"88.4 lb","brand":{"@type":"Brand","name":"Samsung"},"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"3.9","reviewCount":86},"offers":{"@type":"Offer","url":"https://www.homedepot.com/p/Samsung-24-in-4-0-cu-ft-Vented-Smart-Dial-Electric-Dryer-in-White-with-Sensor-Dry-DV25B6900EW/323095575","priceCurrency":"USD","price":989,"priceValidUntil":"04/29/2026","priceSpecification":{"@type":"UnitPriceSpecification","priceType":"https://schema.org/StrikethroughPrice","price":1099,"priceCurrency":"USD"},"hasMerchantReturnPolicy":{"@type":"MerchantReturnPolicy","applicableCountry":"US","returnPolicyCategory":"https://schema.org/MerchantReturnNotPermitted"}},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"CHRIS"},"headline":null,"reviewBody":"The Samsung compact washer and dryer is an excellent laundry combo for tight spaces. Both units provide plenty of space for the cleaning needs of 1-2 people. The multiple settings accommodate all laundry types, and it's a breeze to use. While I don't recommend stuffing your comforter (take those to a dry cleaner or use an industrial machine), for everything else it's great. \r\n\r\nI also had the Home Depot team picknup my old machine and install the new ones. The delivery and installation teams I worked with were great: punctual, communicative, efficient, and pleasant."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sturat"},"headline":"Samsung washer combo","reviewBody":"[This review was collected as part of a promotion.] We love our washer, dryer combo, priced well and very efficient. I highly recommend getting the Samsung washer combo."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"ADMOORE"},"headline":"Capable dryer","reviewBody":"[This review was collected as part of a promotion.] Pairs beautifully with the Samsung washer\nGiving 4 stars because I’d really prefer gas but not available in this size.\nElectric dryers are slower …."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":1,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"annoyedbuyer"},"headline":"\"Ventless\" marketing is a scam","reviewBody":"Did it dry my clothes? Yes. But it took 2 hours. It also heated my bathroom. After drying a full load in two hours, my bathroom (medium-size approx. 8' by 7') would heat up by 15 degrees. While these are marketed as \"ventless\" because there is no vent that pumps the hot air out using ducting, there are heat vents on the back of the dryer that let out hot air into your room (picture included). And because you can't use ducting to vent the hot air outside, it just heats up your room. The marketing claims the hot air is recycled in the heat pump cycle, and that's how it creates energy efficiency and doesn't require venting. But my experience in reality, is that it turned my bathroom into a sauna."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":1,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"mal"},"headline":"Terrible dryer","reviewBody":"We've had this dryer for almost a year and a few months into using it, we realized that the lint was being pulled through the dryer into the back where it sits on the heating element and burns making all our clothes smell like smoke. We've had to pull the back off and remove the lint from the heating element multiple times. We also have to clean the duct out the connects the dryer to the wall duct once a month to make it actually dry our clothes. It seems the lint trap doesn't work and the fan isn't strong enough to push the lint the correct direction. We've been in contact with Samsung about the problem since the beginning of the year. 7 months later, a crazy number of calls and emails back and forth, and onto our third service visit, nothing has been resolved. I would not advise buying this dryer or trying to rely on Samsung customer service."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":1,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"travel4b"},"headline":"Make sure you don’t plan to side vent your dryer.","reviewBody":"My poor rating reflects the fact that this model is advertised as having side and bottom venting options and includes a side venting kit on the product page.  HOWEVER, the kit does not work, not even close.  I’m guessing it fits Salmsung’s larger capacity dryers but the kit pieces are way too long for this size dryer.  I’ve had to sit one piece in half with an angle grinder and gerrymander the other pieces to get a half way acceptable side venting.  I guess I shouldn’t be surprised as Samsung as several different sized dryers but only sells one side vent kit.  I can’t believe they haven’t addressed this."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":2,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"KA in VA"},"headline":"Would not buy again","reviewBody":"We've had the similar model without the AI and wifi for over 4 years, purchased at our builder's recommendation as we were building a close to passive house. The various drying programs have frequently stopped short of the time initially indicated on the display and not because the clothes are already dry.  And it takes FOREVER to dry queen and king size sheets, cotton blankets, quilts and duvet covers.  It has always taken a long time but now it is taking up to 2 days for the heavier cotton blankets and flannel duvet covers.  I think this is partially due to the fact that they always ball up during the cycle, even if I put dryer balls, extra towels, tennis balls, etc in the drum, so I have to constantly check the machine, unravel the bedding and start the cycle again.  The heat pump condensor fins came bent (as the dryer had been dropped during delivery, had to have a bottom panel replaced, photo attached to review) and even though I clean the fins after every cycle with the provided brush and also vacuum them periodically, I recently discovered when using a flashlight that they were packed with lint, so I'm sure this has caused the increasingly longer drying times for bedding and the other cycles stopping short of the indicated time.  I just spent over two hours trying to cleaning the condensor fins, got out a lot of lint but there is still lint trapped against the condensor that is impossible to clean.  I don't know why you'd design a key part of the machine that is so difficult to keep clean.  The brush that comes with the machine isn't stiff enough or have long enough bristles to get deep into the fins to get all the lint out.  So I would caution against this machine unless you want to spend the time (and get the right tools) to deep clean the condensor fins after every dryer cycle. I'm sure some (all?) of the issues I have with drying times and cleaning the lint might be due to me not noticing that the heat pump condensor fins were bent when the dryer was delivered but if that is the case I'd say it's a design fault if such a critical component can be damaged during delivery.  So if purchasing this machine, I would definitely check the heat condensor fins upon deiivery and ask for a replacement if the fins are bent."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":3,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Laxman"},"headline":"LG Dryer","reviewBody":"I bought LG Washer and Dryer as a set. Color white. But the color of Dryer changed to off-white. The cloths do not dry well. I had to rerun the dryer."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"swaggygabby"},"headline":"Smart Dryer","reviewBody":"[This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I love the style of this dryer, but I thought the door would be more transparent. It is barely transparent but it has a light that you can turn on while in use. Since this is an energy saving dryer, it takes longer to dry things which I had to get used to since my last dryer was not energy efficient. I really like all the different cycles it has. Using a cycle in relation to the type of fabric I am using has really restored the quality of the fabrics. I am amazed! The Smart Things app is a great feature but it needs some updates. For example, I can't see how long a load is going to take before starting the cycle, I can't turn my dryer on or off my with it, etc. There was no instructions on where to drain the vent but I figured it out after my dryer stopped working. It is in the same spot you would put your detergent in the washer. The dryer is advertised as quiet but I think it sounds like the average dryer. My dryer door opens up in the same direction as my washer door which I don't like and I'm hoping can be reversed. I don't have mine stacked. The pros definitely outweigh the cons though. I am very happy to do my laundry with this dryer. I am still exploring new and better ways to do my laundry with it."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4,"bestRating":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Gabby"},"headline":"Smart Dryer","reviewBody":"I love the style of this dryer, but I thought the door would be more transparent. It is barely transparent but it has a light that you can turn on while in use. Since this is an energy saving dryer, it takes longer to dry things which I had to get used to since my last dryer was not energy efficient. I really like all the different cycles it has. Using a cycle in relation to the type of fabric I am using has really restored the quality of the fabrics. I am amazed! The Smart Things app is a great feature but it needs some updates. For example, I can't see how long a load is going to take before starting the cycle, I can't turn my dryer on or off my with it, etc. There was no instructions on where to drain the vent but I figured it out after my dryer stopped working. It is in the same spot you would put your detergent in the washer. The dryer is advertised as quiet but I think it sounds like the average dryer. My dryer door opens up in the same direction as my washer door which I don't like and I'm hoping can be reversed. I don't have mine stacked. The pros definitely outweigh the cons though. I am very happy to do my laundry with this dryer. I am still exploring new and better ways to do my laundry with it."}]}</script>
